PROJECT: Discord AI Auto-Responder Bot
LANGUAGE: Python
ESTIMATED TIME: 4 sessions
WHAT IT WILL DO: A Discord bot that lives in your server, listens to 
messages, sends them to OpenAI's ChatGPT API, and responds with 
intelligent AI-generated answers — automatically.

FOLDER STRUCTURE:
discord-ai-bot/
├── bot.py          (main bot file — runs everything)
├── ai.py           (handles talking to OpenAI)
├── .env            (stores your secret keys safely)
└── requirements.txt (lists packages your project needs)

BUILD STAGES:
  Stage 1 — The Skeleton    → Create the bot, connect it to Discord, 
                               make it come online
  Stage 2 — The Ears        → Teach the bot to listen to messages in 
                               your server
  Stage 3 — The Brain       → Connect OpenAI so the bot can generate 
                               smart responses
  Stage 4 — The Polish      → Add error handling, a command prefix to 
                               control when it responds, and clean up

CONCEPTS YOU WILL LEARN:
  - How Discord bots work (tokens, intents, events)
  - Environment variables (keeping secrets safe)
  - Async/await (how Python handles waiting for responses)
  - Working with external APIs (OpenAI)
  - Reading and responding to events in real time
  - Error handling and user experience
